definitions.definition: The organic chemical compound propylene . An alkene which is a colorless gaseous (at room temperature and pressure ) hydrocarbon with the chemical formula C 3 H 6 .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry , official IUPAC name ) The organic chemical compound propylene . An alkene which is a colorless gaseous (at room temperature and pressure ) hydrocarbon with the chemical formula C 3 H 6 .
